The paper deals with the problem of discovering common motifs in time series data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes a new method called CASC, which is based on a large optimization problem and a greedy alternating minimization-based approach. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), and possibly also social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
